The paper deals with natural language understanding and reasoning, which are core topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on solving the Winograd Schema Challenge, which is a task in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of graph-based representations and additional knowledge also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper deals with reasoning and constraints, which are also relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR).
